control. Also, your kids would get the type of education delivered by teachers who are in some cases, hostile to learning. And despite the theme of this woman, there'd be little you could do about it. Why do people like me, product of non-public schools in my youth, exhaust my possibilities of a comfortable retirement just to keep my kids out of schools that are bad and won't get better? Because people like her rationalize their desires and won't face the real problems of public schools. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="800" language="en" documentId="3182" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="tbc343" date="Aug 29, 2013 7:36PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="3" thumbsDown="0" origId="3182" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="800"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>